                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="13494301" author="ben.craig" created="Fri, 9 Nov 2012 20:49:46 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Guarding increase_max_fds definition with HAVE_SYS_RESOURCE_H&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13789712" author="jensg" created="Tue, 8 Oct 2013 21:23:14 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Since you are ifdef&apos;ing the whole function away: Would it make sense to ifdef the prototype in the header file too?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13789723" author="ben.craig" created="Tue, 8 Oct 2013 21:31:23 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I can do that.  In either case, you will get an error if you call increase_max_fds without HAVE_SYS_RESOURCE_H.  Guarding it in the header means that clients get a compiler time error instead of a link time error.  I will update accordingly.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13789767" author="ben.craig" created="Tue, 8 Oct 2013 22:03:46 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Updated from svn patch, and now guarding the prototype&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13790753" author="jensg" created="Wed, 9 Oct 2013 19:31:21 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;+1&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
